//Write a algorithm to rotate the elements of a given array of integers (length 4 ) in left direction and return the new array.

Input: Array of integers {1,2,3,4}

Output: Array of integers {2,3,4,1}

Step 1: Initialize an array of integers with length 4.

int[] arr = {1,2,3,4};

Step 2: Store the first element of the array in a temporary variable.

int temp = arr[0];

Step 3: Shift all the elements of the array to the left by one position.

for(int i=0; i<arr.length-1; i++) {
     arr[i] = arr[i+1];
}

Step 4: Set the value of the last element of the array to the value of the temporary variable.

arr[arr.length-1] = temp;

Step 5: Print the rotated array.

for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++) {
     System.out.print(arr[i] + " ");
}
